5C%22134fe6b9-dea5-45b5-8a0d-f52f570fa777%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETepid%20hiring%20could%20spread%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFlowers%20said%20that%20some%20of%20the%20sluggishness%20that%20has%20afflicted%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-threaten-jobs-of-coders-who-dont-shift-their-focus-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20hiring%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20years%C2%A0could%20overtake%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20a%20few%20areas%20that%20had%20been%20strong%2C%20like%20healthcare%2C%20are%20likely%20to%20remain%20so.%20Yet%20industries%20that%20had%20been%20relative%20bright%20spots%2C%20including%20retail%2C%20transportation%20and%20warehousing%2C%20and%20some%20corners%20of%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%94%20one%20purported%20domestic%20beneficiary%20of%20tariffs%20%E2%80%94%20could%20get%20whacked%2C%20Flowers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20employers%20are%20already%20bringing%20on%20workers%20at%20the%20slowest%20pace%20in%20nearly%20a%20decade%2C%20Stahle%20said.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20the%20number%20of%20job%20postings%20in%20the%20US%20has%20declined%2C%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20December%2C%20listings%20had%20risen%20to%20about%2012%25%20above%20their%20pre-COVID-19%20levels%2C%20Stahle%20said.%20Then%2C%20from%20early%20January%20to%20the%20end%20of%20March%2C%20openings%20drifted%20downward%20to%20about%208.2%25%20above%20their%20pre-pandemic%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2225801bd4-7e92-4b8a-8773-351c12815f21%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESilver%20linings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFlowers%20said%20industries%20like%20finance%2C%20insurance%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20professional%20services%2C%20which%20he%20said%20have%20been%20experiencing%20a%20%26quot%3Bwhite-collar%20recession%26quot%3B%20for%20two%20to%20three%20years%2C%20might%20not%20get%20hit%20as%20hard%20because%20they're%20already%20somewhat%20weak%20and%20because%20the%20impact%20of%20tariffs%20might%20be%20indirect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20bright%20spot%20is%20that%20overall%20layoffs%20remain%20low%2C%20even%20with%20broad%20cuts%20in%20the%20offing%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-checks-doge-firings-trump-delay-benefits-payments-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Flowers%20said%2C%20the%20biggest%20impact%20on%20workers%20could%20come%20from%20lackluster%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20job%20cuts%20because%20of%20these%20tariffs%2C%20but%20almost%20proportionally%20more%20impactful%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20won't%20be%20hiring%20because%20of%20these%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlowers%20said%20in%20a%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20where%20tariff%20retaliation%20spills%20into%20a%20tit-for-tat%20global%20trade%20war%2C%20layoffs%20would%20be%20likely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20steepness%20of%20the%20tariff%20rates%20have%20spooked%20investors%20and%20have%20spooked%20business%20leaders%2C%26quot%3B%20Flowers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20impact%20will%20be%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20job%20and%20spending%20cuts%20the%20White%20House%20is%20attempting%20to%20make%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployers-looking-to-hire-laid-off-federal-workers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20agencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20the%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20advisory%20group%20run%20by%20Elon%20Musk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20White%20House%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%20that%20tariffs%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Bcritical%26quot%3B%20part%20of%20the%20president's%20economic%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20administration%20is%20also%20slashing%20regulations%2C%20pushing%20tax%20cuts%2C%20and%20unleashing%20American%20energy%20to%20drive%20down%20energy%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20poli