eowners-insurance-cost%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsurance%20premiums%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20average%20cost%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-insurance-wildfires-hurricane-climate-disaster-treasury-department-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20insurance%20is%20rising%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20nearly%20every%20ZIP%20code%20across%20America%2C%20new%20research%20shows%20that%20the%20biggest%20percentage%20increases%20between%202021%20and%202024%20were%20in%20Utah%2C%20Illinois%2C%20Arizona%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20and%20Nebraska.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPremiums%20have%20been%20rising%20faster%20in%20Heartland%20states%20than%20coastal%20states%2C%26quot%3B%20Douglas%20Heller%2C%20director%20of%20insurance%20at%20the%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%20and%20coauthor%20of%20the%20research%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20show%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Fdropped-home-insurance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20affordability%20crisis%20extends%20far%20beyond%20Gulf%20Coast%20states%20prone%20to%20hurricanes%20and%20flooding%20or%20California%20towns%20vulnerable%20to%20wildfires%20%E2%80%94%20which%20often%20make%20the%20headlines.%20Extreme%20thunderstorms%20with%20wind%2C%20rain%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhail-stone-storm-damage-threat-to-american-homes-insurance-premiums-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehail%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20also%20causing%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20losses%20in%20states%20between%20the%20slopes%20of%20the%20Rocky%20and%20Appalachian%20mountains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disasters%2C%20combined%20with%20inflation%20and%20the%20rising%20costs%20of%20rebuilding%20homes%2C%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-insurance-wildfires-hurricane-climate-disaster-treasury-department-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edriving%20up%20premiums%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20forcing%20some%20insurance%20companies%20to%20scale%20back%20coverage%20in%20risky%20areas%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F20-counties-where-home-insurers-dropping-most-customers-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrop%20customers%20altogether%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20consequences%20could%20be%20significant%20because%20most%20Americans%20can't%20get%20a%20mortgage%20without%20home%20insurance%2C%20and%20areas%20deemed%20too%20risky%20to%20cover%20could%20see%20property%20values%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FbLqfK%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Changes%20in%20home%20insurance%20premiums%20from%202021%20to%202024%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22515%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20insurance%20crisis%20is%20not%20a%20coastal%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20Heller%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20Republican%20or%20Democratic%20state%20crisis.%20It's%20touching%20every%20corner%20of%20the%20country.%20These%20dramatic%20rate%20hikes%20are%20making%20this%20critical%20tool%20of%20financial%20security%20inaccessible%20because%20it's%20too%20costly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2297b3126c-09ad-40ae-a0fa-911454cd214b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20home%20insurance%20premiums%20are%20rising%20so%20quickly%20in%20many%20states%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%20found%20that%20between%202021%20and%202024%2C%20average%20home%20insurance%20premiums%20in%20Utah%20jumped%2059%25%20to%20nearly%20%241%2C800%20a%20year.%20In%20Arizona%2C%20they%20rose%2048%25%20to%20more%20than%20%242%2C200%20while%20Illinois%20saw%20a%2050%25%20spike%20to%20nearly%20%242%2C950.%20In%20Pennsylvania%2C%20average%20premiums%20rose%2044%25%20to%20nearly%20%242%2C000%2C%20and%20in%20Nebraska%2C%20they%20rose%2035%25%20to%20%245%2C127.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlorida%20has%20the%20highest%20premium%20in%20absolute%20dollars%2C%20averaging%20nearly%20%249%2C500%20in%202024%2C%20but%20its%20average%20rates%20rose%20by%20a%20smaller%20percentage%20compared%20to%20some%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJ.P.%20Morgan%20published%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpmorgan.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fjpm%2Fcib%2Fdocuments%2FWeathering_the_storm.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20March%2031%20that%20similarly%20found%20states%2C%20including%20Colorado%2C%20Utah%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20Iowa%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20and%20Illinois%2C%20experienced%20the%20largest%20percentage%20increases%20in%20home%20insurance%20costs%20between%202019%20and%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeadly%20thunderstorms%20with%20high-speed%20winds%2C%20rain%2C%20hail%2C%20and%20tornadoes%20%E2%80%94%20what%20scientists%20call%20%26quot%3Bsevere%20convective%20storms%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20have%20ripped%20across%20a%20wide%20swath%20of%20the%20Midwest%20and%20the%20South%20this%20year.%20In%202020%2C%20thunderstorms%20caused%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weather.gov%2Find%2F2020derechoanniv%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20%2411%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20damage%20after%20tearing%20through%20states%20including%20South%20Dakota%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20Illinois%2C%20and%20Indiana%2C%20according%20to%20a%20federal%20tally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20those%20big%20losses%20happening%20in%20the%20Heartland%20are%20from%20severe%20convective%20storms%2C%20and%20those%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20driving%20premium%20increases%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarah%20Kapnick%2C%20global%20head%20of%20climate%20advisory%20at%20J.P%20Morgan%20who%20authorized%20its%20report%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20scientists%20have%20long%20warned%20that%20wildfires%2C%20drought%2C%20and%20hurricanes%20are%20becoming%20more%20frequent%20and%20destructive%20as%20the%20planet%20warms%20mostly%20due%20to%20carbon%20emissions%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKapnick%20said%20it's%20more%20challenging%20to%20determine%20the%20climate%20connection%20to%20the%20convective%20storms%20and%20future%20risks%20because%20they%20are%20more%20local.%20Climate%20models%20often%20don't%20capture%20weather%20events%20on%20such%20a%20granular%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientific%20research%20is%20starting%20to%20get%20stronger.%20Kapnick%20cited%20a%20study%20suggesting%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3De890f2c547e03b8d1828aa3f44d6a2c1f9a1082e1394c0d96833299f21f95d2a%26postID%3D67eea2a518fa5330630a5766%26postSlug%3Dhome-insurance-premiums-cost-midwest-great-plains-heartland-2025-4%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41612-024-00728-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehailstones%20will%20get%20bigger%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0due%20to%20climate%20change.%20However%2C%20research%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.noaa.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-10%2FTornadoes_Climate_OnePager_July2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estops%20short%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20connecting%20historical%20changes%20in%20tornadoes%20to%20a%20warming%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKapnick%20said%20insurance%20premiums%20are%20also%20rising%20fast%20in%20Heartland%20states%20because%20their%20markets%20are%20less%20regulated%20compared%20to%20places%20like%20California%2C%20which%20limits%20how%20much%20insurers%20can%20hike%20rates.%20National%20insurers%20can%20pool%20risk%20across%20states%20and%20raise%20premiums%20in%20place%20with%20fewer%20cost%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2241cd5855-ae9f-4c8f-bbc9-7caed65b191a%5C%22%3EThe%20home%20insurance%20crisis%20is%20expected%20to%20worsen%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Heller%20said%20it's%20hard%20to%20capture%20the%20full%20causes%20and%20scale%20of%20the%20home%20insurance%20crisis%20because%20there%20isn't%20much%20publicly%20available%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20annual%20premiums%20in%20his%20report%20don't%20reflect%20what%20customers%20actually%20paid.%20His%20group%20purchased%20%26quot%3Btest%20quotes%26quot%3B%20from%20Quadrant%20Information%20Services%2C%20which%20maintains%20an%20up-to-date%20database%20of%20rates%20and%20pricing%20algorithms%20from%20most%20of%20the%20nation's%20major%20insurance%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20test%20quotes%20are%20created%20by%20plugging%20a%20typical%20homeowner%20into%20pricing%20algorithms%20that%20insurance%20companies%20filed%20with%20state%20regulators%20between%20December%202021%20and%20August%202024.%20Heller%20said%20all%20quotes%20in%20his%20report%20were%20based%20on%20a%20consumer%20with%20a%20mid-tier%20credit%20score%20and%20a%20home%20with%20a%20%24350%2C000%20replacement%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Treasury%20Department%20and%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Insurance%20Commissioners%20in%20January%20published%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-insurance-wildfires-hurricane-climate-disaster-treasury-department-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20of%20246%20million%20insurance%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20sold%20between%202018%20through%202022%20%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20comprehensive%20look%20to%20date.%20They%20found%20that%20homeowners%20who%20live%20in%20areas%20with%20the%20highest%20expected%20losses%20from%20climate-related%20disasters%20paid%2082%25%20more%20for%20insurance%20than%20those%20in%20areas%20with%20the%20lowest%20expected%20losses.%20Nonrenewal%20rates%20were%20also%20higher%20in%20the%20riskiest%20areas%20and%20insurance%20claims%20are%20frequent%20in%20regions%20affected%20by%20wildfires%20and%20severe%20convective%20storms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20that%20data%20collection%20will%20continue%2C%20Heller%20said.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20home%20insurance%20affordability%20crisis%20will%20likely%20get%20worse%20as%20the%20planet%20warms.%20Since%202013%2C%20the%20United%20States%20has%20recorded%20178%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-climate-change-crisis-extreme-weather-is-costing-you-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebillion-dollar%20disasters%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20five%20times%20the%20amount%20recorded%20in%20the%201980s.%20The%20rising%20disaster%20risks%20led%20some%20insurers%20to%20stop%20selling%20policies%20in%20parts%20of%20Florida%20and%20California%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexperts-palisades-fire-will-worsen-california-insurance-crisis-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20only%20get%20worse%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20wildfires%20decimated%20communities%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Treasury%20Department%20and%20NAIC%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKapnick%20said%20insurance%20companies%20and%20policymakers%20need%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20ensure%20properties%20are%20more%20resilient%20to%20extreme%20weather%20to%20reduce%20damages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20easiest%20indicators%20of%20expected%20loss%20is%2C%20how%20old%20is%20your%20roof%3F%20When%20was%20it%20last%20replaced%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKapnick%20said%20insurers%20could%20offer%20homeowners%20discounts%20if%20they%20invest%20in%20resilience%20and%20states%20can%20also%20fund%20such%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20home%20insurance%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acboudreau%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ecboudreau%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E