or%20her%20neuromuscular%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-medical-costs-baby-boomers-paying-for-cancer-treatment-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisease%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20she's%20unsure%20how%20she'll%20stay%20afloat%20on%20disability.%20Despite%20the%20financial%20worries%2C%20she%20said%20her%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20make%20her%20retirement%20years%20worthwhile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20thing%20I%20have%20is%20my%20legacy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20feel%20really%20down%2C%20I%20drive%20to%20Ohio%20to%20see%20my%20grandkids%20and%20my%20daughters%20and%20get%20hugs%20and%20kisses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20chatting%20with%20people%20about%20the%20emotional%20fulfillment%20%E2%80%94%20or%20lack%20of%20it%20%E2%80%94%20that%20comes%20with%20leaving%20a%20career.%20Given%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkaholics-work-hours-balance-quiet-quitting-high-income-men-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkaholic%3C%2Fa%3E%20gene%20and%20the%20genuine%20enjoyment%20I%20get%20from%20my%20job%2C%20there%20is%20a%20chance%20I%20may%20never%20fully%20retire.%20Even%20if%20I%20get%20to%20a%20point%20where%20I%20can%20comfortably%20ride%20off%20into%20the%20proverbial%20sunset%2C%20I%20might%20not%20want%20to.%20I%20get%20bored%20very%20easily.%20It's%20why%20I've%20taken%20up%20marathon%20running%2C%20created%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-write-trivia-questions-as-a-side-gig-heres-how-i-got-started-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrivia%3C%2Fa%3E%20games%2C%20and%20aim%20to%20visit%20all%2050%20states%20by%20my%2030s.%20I'm%20not%20alone%20in%20this%3A%20Two%20dozen%20of%20the%20people%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20said%20they're%20working%20past%20retirement%20age%20with%20no%20intention%20of%20stopping.%20Many%20said%20that%20even%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillionaire-boomer-retirement-strategies-grow-wealth-saving-regrets-social-security-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillionaires%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20hope%20to%20keep%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELouis%20Belline%2C%2075%2C%20said%20he%20%26quot%3Bfailed%20retirement%26quot%3B%20five%20times.%20Belline%20retired%20in%20the%20mid-2000s%20after%2025%20years%20as%20a%20Delta%20Air%20Lines%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funretired-boomer-keep-working-earn-more-money-mind-active-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epilot%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20returning%20to%20flying%20as%20a%20pilot%20trainer%20and%20earning%20%24130%2C000%20a%20year.%20His%20wife%20happily%20retired%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20the%20Georgia%20couple%20has%20a%20net%20worth%20in%20the%20mid-seven%20figures.%20But%20Belline%20said%20he%20may%20work%20until%20his%20late%2070s%20because%20it%20keeps%20him%20sharp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20hourglass%20with%20two%20faces.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67eedf9663d72727e199240d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Drew%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20see%20people%20retire%20and%20sit%20down%20and%20die%2C%26quot%3B%20Belline%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20concern%20I%20have%20is%20I%20don't%20want%20my%20brain%20to%20atrophy.%20I%20figure%20I%20can%20keep%20trucking%20and%20keep%20up%20with%20these%20younger%20people%20who%20are%20smarter%20than%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20John%2C%20a%20senior%20strategic%20policy%20advisor%20at%20AARP%2C%20said%20he's%20seen%20many%20people%20retire%20enthusiastically%20only%20to%20realize%20they%20were%20bored%20or%20lost%20their%20purpose.%20He%20said%20adjusting%20to%20the%20loss%20can%20be%20tough%2C%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20social%20connection%20in%20retirement%20often%20pushes%20people%20back%20to%20work.%20About%20half%20of%20respondents%20in%20an%20AARP%20survey%20of%20unretired%20people%20said%20their%20decision%20to%20return%20to%20work%20was%20based%20on%20having%20%26quot%3Ba%20purpose%20in%20life%2C%20a%20social%20network%2C%20and%20getting%20out%20of%20the%20house.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20retirees%20I%20spoke%20with%20were%20able%20to%20get%20creative%20in%20how%20they%20found%20purpose.%20Aida%20Porras%2C%2067%2C%20lost%20her%20mother%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20and%20cared%20for%20her%20husband%20for%20five%20years%20after%20his%20stage%20four%20cancer%20diagnosis.%20She'd%20been%20laid%20off%20from%20her%20job%20as%20a%20healthcare%20consultant%20and%20had%20focused%20her%20attention%20on%20caring%20for%20her%20ailing%20mother.%20while%20providing%20consultation%20as%20an%20independent%20contractor.%20After%20her%20husband%20died%2C%20Porras%20took%20over%20the%20family%20art%20supply%20business%20in%20Georgia%2C%20which%20gave%20her%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasked-retired-neighbor-favor-friendship-family-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20circle%20of%20friends%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sparked%20her%20interest%20in%20painting%2C%20and%20allowed%20her%20to%20flex%20her%20entrepreneurial%20muscles.%20It%20also%20helped%20her%20overcome%20her%20grief%20and%20stay%20focused%20on%20life's%20joys.%20She%20said%20she%20doesn't%20have%20a%20transition%20plan%20for%20her%20retirement%2C%20adding%20that%20many%20in%20her%20family%20lived%20into%20their%2090s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'll%20have%20some%20extra%20cash%2C%20which%20will%20help%20me%20down%20the%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20Porras%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20when%20I%20go%20to%20bed%2C%20I%20laugh%20and%20say%2C%20'Nobody%20can%20fire%20me.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHearing%20stories%20like%20Porras'%20and%20dozens%20of%20others%20made%20me%20realize%20that%20even%20if%20I%20don't%20hit%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoney-lessons-wish-learned-wealthy-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20milestones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20could%20always%20pivot%20and%20open%20a%20business%2C%20write%20a%20book%2C%20or%20even%20take%20on%20blue-collar%20work.%20There%20will%20always%20be%20something%20to%20give%20me%20financial%20and%20personal%20fulfillment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20most%20important%20factor%20for%20a%20successful%20retirement%20seemed%20to%20be%20having%20a%20clear%20understanding%20of%20what%20makes%20me%20happy.%20In%20my%20interviews%2C%20many%20people%20said%20they%20were%20too%20ambitious%20upon%20retiring%20and%20blew%20through%20their%20reserves%20too%20fast%2C%20while%20others%20said%20they%20were%20too%20cautious%20and%20sacrificed%20their%20enjoyment.%20People%20who%20considered%20their%20retirement%20successful%20agreed%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretire-early-unretire-financial-independence-fire-start-business-regrets-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20about%20fulfillment%20and%20purpose%2C%20whether%20realizing%20travel%20goals%2C%20finishing%20that%20last%20professional%20achievement%2C%20or%20having%20coffee%20weekly%20with%20a%20longtime%20friend.%20As%20someone%20who%20has%20frequently%20sacrificed%20my%20enjoyment%20to%20get%20further%20ahead%20financially%2C%20such%20as%20working%20a%20full-time%20job%20most%20semesters%20of%20college%2C%20I'm%20starting%20to%20do%20less%20in%20my%20spare%20time%2C%20backing%20off%20some%20commitments%20while%20prioritizing%20travel%20and%20health%20(though%20I'm%20not%20ignoring%20recent%20market%20moves%20entirely).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20conversations%20have%20given%20me%20some%20pretty%20good%20models%20for%20what%20a%20truly%20successful%20retirement%20may%20look%20like.%20Take%20Bill%20